## Admin Page Layout Rule ⚠️ CRITICAL

**Admin pages under `src/app/admin/` must NOT use `DashboardLayout`.**

The admin layout (`src/app/admin/layout.tsx`) wraps all admin routes with `AdminShell` → `DashboardLayout`. Adding `DashboardLayout` in individual admin pages causes duplicate sidebar and header.

### ✅ CORRECT - Admin page structure
```typescript
export default function AdminEntityPage() {
  return (
    <div className="container mx-auto px-4 py-8 max-w-7xl">
      {/* Page content */}
    </div>
  );
}
```

### ❌ WRONG - Causes duplicate layout
```typescript
import { DashboardLayout } from '@/components/layouts/app-layout';
export default function AdminEntityPage() {
  return (
    <DashboardLayout>  {/* WRONG - AdminShell already provides this */}
      <div className="container mx-auto px-4 py-8 max-w-7xl">...</div>
    </DashboardLayout>
  );
}
```

**Auto-generation**: `complete-entity-generator.ts`, `navigation-generator.ts`, and `app-state-sync-generator.ts` (admin-page-template) must generate admin pages without DashboardLayout.

